snippet.textDisplay: Kon I need some help, I'm in year 11starting college soon living in West London and for a couple years now I've been wanting to find a career to do with film or photography where I'm the one behind the camera shooting every thing, so basically like a camera man. How ever I've recently been looking at local colleges around me and the courses for what I want to do expect grades to high for me, aren't exactly the right stuff for what it want to do in my career later on, and most of them expect me to already have some sort of experience in film but I have none other than that I'm currently studying film studies in school for gcses but my expected grade for it is level 3 which in the English grade system is pretty much useless... So I've had to take another route in which career I will have to take when I'm older and just followed my freinds into car mechanics as I'm not sure what to do any more and kind of stuck in an awkward position in life now. I'm not looking for people to give me motivation like "come on man study harder and you'll succeed your dreams" as realistically all my grades are too low to get expected grades from most jobs or what ever but instead I'm looking for advice as to what I should to look for to get the career I want. Maybe Kon has some jobs he could let me help out with that would get me some experience or if he knows people that could teach me and possibly get me a job in film. I have also looked into apprenticeships but I don't think my grades would be high enough for any of them to accept me so I'm really stuck in a position where I might just have to ignore that idea and dream of my career in film go and just follow my freinds into car mechanics where I'm not that interested. I'm not trying to sound like a begger I'm just really stressed and confused on what to do next and really need strong advise, ideas and hope as to move forward into what I want in life.
